<TITLE> Lacklustre Eid behind bars </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 14 (bdnews24.com)  Relatives visited former prime ministers Khaleda Zia and Sheikh Hasina in special jails Sunday as they celebrated an apparently lacklustre Eid behind bars. After Eid prayers, adherents of the BNP chairperson and the Awami League president flocked to the Sangsad Bhaban complex amid tight security. The VIP prisonersformer ministers and lawmakersoffered prayers under a special arrangement. Prison authorities arranged special food for the VIP and the common prisoners. They were also meeting with their loved ones. Deputy inspector general (prisons) Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com they had arranged special food for Khaleda and Hasina, who are celebrating the premier festival for the first time behind bars. They had vermicelli and puffed rice in the morning; rice, fish and fruit for lunch and will have polao , beef or mutton, sweets for dinner. "They can eat chicken if they wish," he said. AL general secretary Abdul Jalil, Khaleda's younger son Arafat Rahman Coco and 13 other high-profile prisoners are celebrating Eid at Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Rahman Medical University hospital and other hospitals and clinics. The Eid congregation for the ordinary prisoners was held inside the Dhaka Central Jail at 7:45am. Mohammed Oliullah led the jamaat . Inspector general (prisons) Brig Gen Zakir Hassan and other top prisons officials also attended it. Another congregation was held for VIP prisoners near Karnaphuli Cell at 8:45am, led by Hafez Abul Kashem. Some 50 VIP prisoners, including Khaleda's other son Tarique Rahman and former BNP minister Dr Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain joined the jamaat . Zakir Hassan told the reporters, "As part of the prison reforms, different jails are observing Eid. The prisoners were given new dresses and special food." The prisoners can also buy food from the canteen and prison authorities will check the food the relatives would send for them, he said. Siddiqui, the DIG, prisons, said they had arranged special security for the Eid jamaat , drafting in additional jailors. bdnews24
